AB  -  Objective: Our objective was to study the effect of furosemide on postpartum BP recovery in women with hypertensive disorders of pregnancy (HDP). Study Design: Randomized, double‐blind, placebo controlled trial of women with HDP (gestational HTN and preeclampsia with/without severe features) from June 2018 to October 2019. Women with contraindications to furosemide or current use were excluded. Women were randomized to 5 days oral furosemide 20 mg or placebo on postpartum day 1 and were enrolled in text based home BP monitoring. Primary outcomes: persistently elevated BP at 7 days postpartum (defined as ≥48 hours of BP >140/90) and days to BP resolution. Secondary outcomes: additional hypertensive medication after discharge, and HTN related readmissions/ER visits. Generalized linear models were used to calculate adjusted relative risk, Kaplan Meier curves were used for time to BP resolution. Results were stratified by disease severity. Results: We randomized 384 women (192/group). Baseline characteristics were similar except cesarean rate was higher for the furosemide group (29% vs. 20%, p=0.04). Approximately 75% were Black, mean BMI was 36.1, and 66% had non‐severe HDP. There was a 60% reduction in the prevalence of women with persistently elevated BP at 7 days in the furosemide group (6% vs. 14%, aRR 0.40, p=0.01). The magnitude of reduction was greater (74%) in women with non‐severe HDP (Table 1). Days to BP resolution was not different between groups overall (10 vs 10.5, p=0.12) but was significantly shorter among non‐severe women (8.5 vs. 10.5, p=0.001) in the furosemide group. There was a 40% reduction in need for hypertensive medication after discharge in the furosemide group (13% vs. 20%, aRR 0.61 p=0.03). There was no significant difference in HTN related readmissions/ER visits. Figure 1 demonstrates the differences in predicted BP postpartum (a) overall and (b) stratified by severity. Conclusion: In this RCT, postpartum furosemide significantly improved BP control in women with HDP, mostly in women with non‐severe HDP. Routine use of furosemide postpartum should be considered in women with HDP. [Formula presented] [Formula presented]
